meanings: 짱 [jjang] is already a widely-known Korean slang word. It means “best”, “top of top” or “super” in most cases and is used as a noun in sentences like this; “이거 짱이에요”. And it also means “very” or “really” as an adverb in sentences like “짱 멋있어요”.
